sequenceDiagram
  %% Diagram 08: CQRS Read Path - Query Handler to Materialized Views

  autonumber
  actor U as Client
  participant G as API Gateway
  participant QB as Query Bus
  participant QH as Query Handler
  participant C as Redis Cache
  participant RV as Read Replica / Materialized Views
  participant MS as Meilisearch
  participant O as Observability

  U->>G: HTTPS Query Request (e.g., GetVendorDashboardQuery)
  G->>QB: Authenticated query dispatch
  QB->>QH: Execute query

  QH->>C: Check cache key
  alt Cache hit
    C-->>QH: Cached DTO
    QH-->>QB: Return response DTO
    QB-->>G: 200 + trace/correlation ID
    G-->>U: Query response (low latency)
  else Cache miss
    alt Query requires full-text search
      QH->>MS: Search index query
      MS-->>QH: Ranked search docs
      QH->>RV: Read supporting projection fields
      RV-->>QH: Projection rows
    else Query is analytics/history lookup
      QH->>RV: Read projection/materialized view
      alt Read source unavailable
        RV-->>QH: Timeout or unavailable
        QH->>C: Try stale snapshot fallback
        C-->>QH: Last known response + stale marker
        QH->>O: Emit degraded read-path telemetry
        QH-->>QB: Return degraded response DTO
        QB-->>G: 200 + stale-response marker
        G-->>U: Query response (degraded)
      else Read source available
        RV-->>QH: Projection rows
      end
    end

    QH->>QH: Compose response DTO (no writes)
    QH->>C: Refresh cache with TTL
    QH-->>QB: Return response DTO
    QB-->>G: 200 + trace/correlation ID
    G-->>U: Query response
  end

  Note over QH,C: Read path is side-effect free on command model
  Note over C: TTL policy: forecast 24h, category 1h, weather 6h, opportunity 15m
